\begin_layout Section
Numerical Results
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this section we present the results of the numerical modeling of sample
 structures using the models presented in this and previous chapters.
 As before, we investigate the optical properties of a 
\begin_inset Formula $200\,\AA$
\end_inset

 wide 
\begin_inset Formula $GaAs$
\end_inset

 well, surrounded by 
\begin_inset Formula $Ga_{0.9}Al_{0.1}As$
\end_inset

 barriers with 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

-doped layers introduced at 
\begin_inset Formula $1000\,\AA$
\end_inset

 away from the barrier-well boundaries.
 We investigate optical susceptibility, refractive index, absorbtion and
 spontanious emission properties of this structure at various ambient temperatur
e and doping conditions.
 Along with the variation of the physical parameters of the discussed models,
 we investigate the influance of the various phenomenological parameters
 of the models on the optical properties.
 
\end_layout

